{"id":32737,"date":"2024-01-24T20:53:30","date_gmt":"2022-03-24T15:23:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=32737"},"modified":"2023-01-30T21:44:42","modified_gmt":"2023-01-30T16:14:42","slug":"how-to-clean-pooja-room-vessels","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/housekeeping\/how-to-clean-pooja-room-vessels\/","title":{"rendered":"6 Time-Tested Tricks To Keep Your Pooja Room Squeaky Clean"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>All the hacks and tricks you need to know about how to keep your pooja room clean<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Pooja rooms are an integral part of most Indian households. Many believe that a home is a mere brick and mortar building until it\u2019s completed with a temple of god inside it. For centuries, the pooja room has been believed to have the home&#8217;s soul. Therefore, keeping it clean and tidy is essential. But it is also true that some regularly used pooja items like flowers, leaves, rangolis, incense sticks and diyas can often make this holy place look quite dirty. So, if you\u2019ve been wondering how to keep your pooja room clean, here are easy tricks that can prove exceptionally helpful to keep the pooja room clean at all times.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean Brass Pooja Items<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In most Indian households, idols of gods and goddesses, lamps and incense stick holders are usually made of brass. While they are pleasant to look at, brass tends to easily get sticky and grimy with oil. It also oxidises pretty quickly. You can keep brass items clean in three easy ways:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Rub brass items with a lemon slice. Use cold water to wash away the grime before drying them with a clean cloth.<\/li><li>Coat the lemon slice with baking soda and then rub it on the brass item for tough stains.<\/li><li>Alternatively, you can use tamarind pulp to clean brass items, rinse the grime away with warm water, and towel dry it.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24194928\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-with-brass.jpg\" alt=\"How to clean pooja vessels made up of brass where acidity can wash away grime from brassware\" class=\"wp-image-32738\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24194928\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-with-brass.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24194928\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-with-brass-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24194928\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-with-brass-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24194928\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-with-brass-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Acidity can wash away grime from brassware<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean Copper Pooja Vessels<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Copper is a reactive material. If exposed to water or oxygen for a long time, it reacts and forms copper oxide, commonly known as tarnish. It is green in colour. That\u2019s why items made of copper discolour and develop dark spots. So, if you are wondering how to clean pooja room vessels made of copper, worry not. These are some easy ways to do it:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Sprinkle some salt on half a lemon and scrub your copper items with this. Later, wash it with warm water.<\/li><li>Make a paste of equal parts table salt and vinegar. Use a toothbrush or rough cloth to scrub your copper idols and vessels thoroughly.<\/li><li>If the stain is tough, we suggest you boil the copper items in vinegar and salt solution for 15 minutes before wiping them dry.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195614\/how-to-clean-copper-pooja-vessels.jpg\" alt=\"How to clean copper pooja vessels\" class=\"wp-image-32739\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195614\/how-to-clean-copper-pooja-vessels.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195614\/how-to-clean-copper-pooja-vessels-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195614\/how-to-clean-copper-pooja-vessels-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195614\/how-to-clean-copper-pooja-vessels-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Vinegar is a popular cleaning agent for copperware<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean Silver Pooja Items<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Many households use figurines and other pooja essentials like lamps, receptacles for sacred ash and bells made of silver. But like copper, silver tarnishes quickly and becomes black. Here\u2019s how you can clean silver pooja items easily:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Scrub silver items with toothpaste.<\/li><li>Alternatively, you can put some baking soda into boiling water and put a tiny scrap of aluminium foil into it. Dip your silver pooja items in the solution for 10 seconds, and voila, they will shine like new!<\/li><li>You can also use sacred ash or vibhuti to restore the shine to your silver pooja samagri.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195841\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-made-up-of-silver.jpg\" alt=\"How to clean pooja vessels made up of silver with vibhuti\" class=\"wp-image-32740\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195841\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-made-up-of-silver.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195841\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-made-up-of-silver-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195841\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-made-up-of-silver-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24195841\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-made-up-of-silver-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Keep your silver pooja items clean with vibhuti<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Wipe The Pooja Room Door Twice A Week<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In most cases, pooja room doors are made of intricately carved wood or jaali patterns. Both tend to accumulate dust in the nooks and crevices, making the pooja room look dirty if not maintained properly. Dip a cotton ball into olive oil to clean it. This will give the pooja room door in your home a new life.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24201759\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-to-wipe-the-pooja-room-door-twice-a-week.jpg\" alt=\"How to clean pooja vessels and wipe the pooja room door twice a week\" class=\"wp-image-32741\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24201759\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-to-wipe-the-pooja-room-door-twice-a-week.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24201759\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-to-wipe-the-pooja-room-door-twice-a-week-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24201759\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-to-wipe-the-pooja-room-door-twice-a-week-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24201759\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-to-wipe-the-pooja-room-door-twice-a-week-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Add glaze to your pooja room door with olive oil<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Clean Pooja Room Tiles<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Marble is the most commonly used material to build a pooja room in India. Though, tiles are also seen in many homes. Maintaining the polish of marble and tiles in pooja rooms can be quite challenging, given the constant exposure to elements like heat, oil and ash. Here are some tips on how to clean pooja room tiles:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>You can use a mixture of lemon juice and baking powder to clean marble tiles in the pooja room.<\/li><li>Alternatively, you can add baking powder and dishwashing liquid diluted in warm water and wipe the stains off the marble and tiles.<\/li><li>Oxalic acid is also great to clean marble. Rub the powder on the marble surface with a damp cloth to scrub it clean.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24202649\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-tiles.jpg\" alt=\"How to clean pooja vessels and tiles which need regular cleaning\" class=\"wp-image-32742\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24202649\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-tiles.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24202649\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-tiles-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24202649\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-tiles-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24202649\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-tiles-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Pooja room tiles need regular cleaning<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How To Organise The Pooja Room<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Pooja rooms in Indian households tend to have many loose items just lying here and there. Things like boxes of incense sticks, matchboxes, packets of rangoli, extra cotton thread for diya and oil cans, among others. All of these items can create clutter and grime if not stored properly. Use modular pooja room temples with built-in storage cabinets to keep such items hidden away.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24203219\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-organize-pooja-room.jpg\" alt=\"how to clean pooja vessels and organize which helps to keep the space tidy\" class=\"wp-image-32743\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24203219\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-organize-pooja-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24203219\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-organize-pooja-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24203219\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-organize-pooja-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/24203219\/how-to-clean-pooja-vessels-and-organize-pooja-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Built-in storage helps to keep the space tidy<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>How did you like these hacks? We hope these tips answer your questions about how to keep a pooja room clean. Follow them to easily keep your pooja room uncluttered, clean and serene. To get your custom-made pooja rooms, feel free to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">contact our designers<\/a> today! To find inspiration for your home renovation, read our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/\">blogs<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Are you looking for traditional pooja room designs?\" src=\"htt